A: You are trying to switch to a window that does not exist. The error message "Unable to locate window" indicates that the window handle you are trying to switch to does not exist.
The window handles are not ordered, they are just unique identifiers. When you call getWindowHandles(), it returns a Set of all the window handles. You can't predict which one will be the first or the second.
You should store the window handles in a list or an array, and then switch to the window handle you want.
Here is an example:
List<String> windowHandles = new ArrayList<String>(driver.getWindowHandles());
driver.switchTo().window(windowHandles.get(1));

This will switch to the second window. If you want to switch to the first window, you would use:
driver.switchTo().window(windowHandles.get(0));


A: You can use the following code to switch between two windows:
Set<String> windowHandles = driver.getWindowHandles();
Iterator<String> iterator = windowHandles.iterator();
String parentWindow = iterator.next(); // get the parent window
String childWindow = iterator.next(); // get the child window

driver.switchTo().window(childWindow); // switch to child window

// perform your operations here

driver.switchTo().window(parentWindow); // switch back to parent window

// perform your operations here

driver.close(); // close the child window

This code will switch to the child window, perform your operations, switch back to the parent window, and then close the child window.

